1. Install Sonarqube community edition
2. Run C:\sonarqube\bin\windows-x86-64\StartSonar.bat on windows
3. Wait few seconds then Open browser: http://localhost:9000
4. Login username: admin
         password: admin
5. Create Project and set Project key: junit-project, token will be generated, copy it
6. add this to pom.xml
<build>
    <plugins>
        <!-- Run JUnit tests -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.apache.maven.plugins</groupId>
            <artifactId>maven-surefire-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>3.2.5</version>
        </plugin>
        <!-- Code coverage -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.jacoco</groupId>
            <artifactId>jacoco-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>0.8.11</version>
            <executions>
                <execution>
                    <goals>
                        <goal>prepare-agent</goal>
                    </goals>
                </execution>
                <execution>
                    <id>report</id>
                    <phase>test</phase>
                    <goals>
                        <goal>report</goal>
                    </goals>
                </execution>
            </executions>
        </plugin>
        <!-- SonarQube -->
        <plugin>
            <groupId>org.sonarsource.scanner.maven</groupId>
            <artifactId>sonar-maven-plugin</artifactId>
            <version>3.10.0.2594</version>
        </plugin>
    </plugins>
</build>
7. Run sonaqube analysis
mvn clean verify sonar:sonar ^
  -Dsonar.projectKey=junit-project ^
  -Dsonar.host.url=http://localhost:9000 ^
  -Dsonar.token=YOUR_TOKEN
8. Verify using http://localhost:9000, the sonarqube report will open

